# 02 — RBAC role assignments (least privilege)

> **Owner: central platform team.** Grants the pilot deploy identity the minimum
> it needs to provision + deploy use-case resources — scoped to the
> **{{RBAC_SCOPE}}** (`{{TARGET_RESOURCE_GROUP}}`), never the subscription and
> never the central hub.

## Principle
- Scope: the target resource group only — `{{RBAC_SCOPE_ID}}`.
- Roles (both at the **same** RG scope — least privilege preserved):
  - `{{RBAC_ROLE}}` — create/manage the use-case resources.
  - `{{RBAC_RA_ADMIN_ROLE}}` (`{{RBAC_RA_ADMIN_ROLE_ID}}`) — keyless Foundry azd
    templates perform `Microsoft.Authorization/roleAssignments/write` during
    `azd provision` to grant the app's managed identity its data-plane roles
    (e.g. *Cognitive Services OpenAI User*, *Search Index Data Contributor*).
    **`{{RBAC_ROLE}}` alone cannot create role assignments**, so provisioning
    fails with `AuthorizationFailed` unless this second role is also granted.
- For `citadel-spoke` posture the pilot consumes the hub via an Access Contract
  (`citadel-spoke-onboarding`); it receives **no** role on hub resources.

## Commands
```bash
# Ensure the target resource group exists (idempotent)
az group create \
  --name {{TARGET_RESOURCE_GROUP}} \
  --subscription {{TARGET_SUBSCRIPTION_ID}} \
  --location {{TARGET_LOCATION}}

# Resolve the UAMI principal (object) id
PRINCIPAL_ID=$(az identity show \
  --name {{UAMI_NAME}} --resource-group {{UAMI_RESOURCE_GROUP}} \
  --query principalId -o tsv)

# 1) Assign the deploy role, scoped to the target resource group ONLY
az role assignment create \
  --assignee-object-id "$PRINCIPAL_ID" \
  --assignee-principal-type ServicePrincipal \
  --role "{{RBAC_ROLE}}" \
  --scope "{{RBAC_SCOPE_ID}}"

# 2) Allow keyless provision to assign data-plane roles within this RG.
#    Optionally add --condition to restrict which roles it may grant.
az role assignment create \
  --assignee-object-id "$PRINCIPAL_ID" \
  --assignee-principal-type ServicePrincipal \
  --role "{{RBAC_RA_ADMIN_ROLE}}" \
  --scope "{{RBAC_SCOPE_ID}}"
```

> Do **not** widen `--scope` to the subscription or to any central-platform
> resource group. See `../central-platform-boundary.md`.
